properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 13 at 7:47PM PST until January 14 at 1:00PM PST by NWS Reno NV
properties.description:
* CHANGES...Updated IMPACTS to reflect concerns for fire weather.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts 55 to 65 mph
expected across the Eastern Sierra. Wind prone areas such as
Lee Vining, Antelope Valley, and near the Mammoth Airport
could see gusts over 70 mph. Sierra crest ridge gusts over 100
mph.

* WHERE...Mono County.

* WHEN...From 10 PM Monday to 1 PM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees, fences, and
power lines. Power outages are possible. Travel will be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Severe
turbulence for aviation with delays and cancellations likely.
Increased potential for enhanced fire danger with the strong
winds and relatively dry conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A few light snow showers are possible
early Tuesday morning resulting in localized slick spots.
properties.instruction:
Now is the time to secure loose outdoor items such as patio
furniture, holiday decorations (if those are really still up),
and trash cans before winds increase which could blow these items
away. The best thing to do is prepare ahead of time by making
sure you have extra food and water on hand, flashlights with
spare batteries and/or candles in the event of a power outage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 PM PST TUESDAY
